defaultMark Burns-Williamson, West Yorkshire PCC, made a commitment in his Police and Crime Plan to listen to communities first:
default&#xa0;
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultTo spend as much of his time as possible listening to the people of West Yorkshire, visiting neighbourhoods, holding surgeries and listening to a wide range of groups about their experiences and what matters to them.
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultTo work with communities on key issues affecting them and put their needs first when making decisions.
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultTo use his staff at the Office of the Police and Crime Commissioner to help him gather people’s views, allowing him to hear the voices of more of the people he has been elected to serve.
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultAbove all else, he will continue to listen to you first.
